</paragraph>
<paragraph id="770EA319FFA6FFE2772EFEB9F75FFE1F" blockId="4.[264,1323,284,510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName id="B0B1D89AFFA6FFE2772EFEB9F44BFEBC" authority="Geisthardt &amp; Day, 2004" authorityName="Geisthardt &amp; Day" authorityYear="2004" box="[312,586,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyroidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="45C57F0BFFA6FFE2772EFEB9F44BFEBC" box="[312,586,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Lampyroidea maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5EF6C270FFA6FFE27442FEB9F4B0FEBF" box="[596,689,324,350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the third Iranian species of this genus. Compared with two other species recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="0FA6E389FFA6FFE274D5FE91F4F4FE67" box="[707,757,364,390]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B0B1D89AFFA6FFE27514FE91F21DFE67" authority="Geisthardt" authorityName="Geisthardt" authorityYear="1988" box="[770,1052,364,390]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyroidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennalis">
<emphasis id="45C57F0BFFA6FFE27514FE91F59AFE64" box="[770,923,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">L. antennalis</emphasis>
Geisthardt
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B0B1D89AFFA6FFE27243FE91F327FE67" authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1907" box="[1109,1318,364,390]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyroidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="45C57F0BFFA6FFE27243FE91F2CBFE64" box="[1109,1226,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">L. persica</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B0B1D89AFFA6FFE2771EFE69F416FE4C" authority="Geisthardt &amp; Day, 2004" authorityName="Geisthardt &amp; Day" authorityYear="2004" box="[264,535,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyroidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="45C57F0BFFA6FFE2771EFE69F416FE4C" box="[264,535,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Lampyroidea maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5EF6C270FFA6FFE27409FE69F478FE4F" box="[543,633,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is much greater in size, has slender antennae, and the apex of the elytra is paler and somewhat reflective. The most important differences are given in table 1.
</paragraph>
